.Sh BUGS
In-progress snapshot actions are not visible via the snapshots endpoint.
Running
.Nm
while a previous snapshot is still being created may trigger a second
snapshot.
Avoid scheduling runs more frequently than once per hour.
.Pp
Only completed snapshots are counted towards the retention limit.
A pending snapshot will not be pruned even if it would exceed the
.Fl k
threshold.
.
.Sh SECURITY CONSIDERATIONS
The API token grants full read and write access to all resources in your
DigitalOcean account.
Store it in
.Pa /etc/periodic.conf
with mode
.Sy 0600
and owned by
.Sy root .
Never pass the token on the command line in a multi-user environment as
it will be visible in
.Xr ps 1
output.
.
.Sh HISTORY
Originally written as a FreeBSD-native rewrite of the
.Nm do-snapshot
project, replacing bash, curl, and Linux-specific conventions with
.Xr sh 1 ,
.Xr fetch 1 ,
and
.Xr periodic 8 .
